Title: Flat connections for Yang-Mills theories on the 3--torus
Authors: Arjan Keurentjes
Comments: 4 pages, LaTeX, 1 figure, uses cargese.cls, contribution to
  proceedings of NATO-ASI and TMR Summer School "Progress in String Theory and
  M-theory", Cargese, May 24 - June 5 1999 (talk by author)
Report-no: INLO-PUB-15/99
\\
  We discuss the moduli space of flat connections of Yang-Mills theories
formulated on T^3 x R, with periodic boundary conditions. When the gauge group
is SO(N>=7), G_2, F_4, E_6, E_7 or E_8, the moduli space consists of more than
one component.
